      "text": "For trade ideas if you want to inverse Jim Cramer on the oil trade:\n\nLong $JETS (US Airliner ETF) 2028 calls where IV is 25%.\n\nIt’s priced low beta (25% IV) but it moved -20% this month.\n\nIndividual long on $DAL or $AAL carries elevated 55%+ IV, while the ETF basically moves relatively around the same rate. \n\nUS is largely insulated regarding oil compared to the rest of the world as well and the ETF is concentrated around US airliners.\n\nNot exactly a very well kept secret airliners move in the opposite direction of oil. \n\nOf course this trade carries risks in the event Jim Cramer, Wallstreetbets, and X doomposters are actually right about $200 oil.\n\nBut given the date, there’s enough time for oil prices to revert to mean + Venezuela production to get rolling.\n\nTLDR: if you want to go the other direction of crude oil, $JETS at sub 30 IV is the best way to go.",
